The paper presents a new graph storage system that focuses on transactional updates and real-time graph analytics. This suggests that the paper could belong to the databases (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), cryptography and security (cs.CR), or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. However, since the paper primarily focuses on graph storage and processing, cs.DB and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The use of a novel graph-aware data structure and concurrency control mechanism also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DC. The potential security implications of the system could also place it in cs.CR, while the focus on real-time graph analytics could place it in cs.SI.
